The independent schools in Scotland have an excellent state of service in the field of academic excellence, and this continued in 2018 with a number of excellent exam results, as well as individual and collective success in sport, art, music and other community-wide initiatives.
With over 30,000 students in Scotland, these schools, represented by The Scottish Council of Independent Schools (SCIS), strive to deliver the best service to their students and parents.
Independent schools strive to prepare their students for further and higher education, the career chosen by them and their place as world citizens.
As an educational sector that can design and implement a custom school curriculum, we see that modern languages remain popular and desirable in schools.
Nelson Mandela said: ‘If you speak to someone in a language he understands, you reach his head.
